==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: December
<hw>De*cem"ber</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧m"b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>prop.
n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧cembre</ets>, from L.
<ets>December</ets>, fr. <ets>decem</ets> ten; this being the tenth
month among the early Romans, who began the year in March. See
<er>Ten</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The twelfth and last month of the
year, containing thirty-one days. During this month occurs the winter
solstice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: With reference to the end of the year and to
the winter season; <as>as, the <ex>December</ex> of his
life</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decembrist</ent>⟦br⟧
